          "body": "Verse 18 is grammatically subordinate to verse 17 — *take the helmet... and the sword... praying at all times*. Prayer is not the seventh piece of armor; it is the atmosphere in which the whole *panoplia* is worn. Four *alls* in one verse: *all prayer*, *all times*, *all perseverance*, *all the saints*. Then Paul makes himself the test case (vv.19-20): even an apostle, even one in chains, needs intercession for *parrēsia* — boldness to speak the *mystery of the gospel* as he ought. The chained ambassador is the chapter's portrait of what the armored believer looks like — restrained outwardly, free inwardly, still speaking."
